text:
The street sandwich called "lomito": The idea is that they prepare it quickly, that it is cheap because it is fast food. You're supposed to eat there on your work break. Don't expect a great flavor, it will be good but not like in a restaurant.

We have "bodegons" there you wil get a lot of food, can be "cheap" or expensive it depends. Some of them offers all you can eat, so ask. (La Bistecca in Puerto Madero its cheap, all you can eat, is not a bodegon but it works like one of them)

Finally you have "gourmet" food, personally i hate it because you will experiment good flavors but not a large amount of food. I feel scammed in those places, but there are people who like that experience. 

Thats Buenos Aires, you will enjoy Bariloche if you like cold weather and snow (you can do snowboard or ski but it is expensive af). Do you want wines? go to Mendoza, there are wines tours.
